  "texts": [
    "We plan to enhance our proposed network by accounting for uncertainty in its predictions.",
    "One approach is to employ the Monte Carlo dropout method, where dropout layers are applied during both training and testing phases [50].",
    "This involves predicting each new input multiple times (K times), and the average of these predictions determines the final class.",
    "Another approach is the use of a Bayesian framework, which allows the model to learn relationships between input data and different types of uncertainty.",
    "This includes aleatoric uncertainty, which captures inherent variability, and the approximation of epistemic uncertainty."
  ],
